28/04/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- If it were held today, Serbia's presidential election would be won by Democratic Party head Boris Tadic, according to a new poll by the Faktor Plus agency. 
The survey, released Tuesday (27 April), found that 24.6 per cent of the public would support Tadic, while 19 per cent would back Tomislav Nikolic of the Serbian Radical Party. 
Ruling coalition candidate Dragan Marsicanin would come in third with 10.9 per cent. 
A fourth candidate, Branislav Ivkovic, will reprensent the Socialist People's Party in the 13 June election. 
(Politica daily, Beta - 27/04/04)
